name: NBA
summary: The NBA Finals have been filled with excitement and intrigue. Game 2 of the series between the Boston Celtics and Dallas Mavericks was the most-watched in five years. The Mavericks won Game 4 by an impressive margin, 122-84, forcing the Celtics to win Game 5 to close out the series. However, the Celtics took the first two games in the series, giving them a 2-0 lead heading into Dallas. The NBA Finals have been a great showcase for young players, including Luka Doncic of the Mavericks. Despite the Mavericks' loss in Game 2, Doncic is still expected to learn and grow from his first NBA Finals experience. The NBA is also looking to the future, with a recent article in The New York Times exploring the league's plans for growth and expansion.
